The “Raise your voice - not your phone” campaign saw Idols SA winner Paxton Fielies and radio DJ Carl Wastie surprise learners and talk to them about the dangers of bullying and the problematic nature of sharing bullying videos on social media. Wastie showed learners the online campaign platform created to educate the youngsters on their responsibility to intervene when bullying took place. The platform also hosts information on victim support for those being bullied and directs them on appropriate action to take. “There are different types of bullying. Physical bullying you see every day and verbal bullying which takes your power away. Bullying becomes viral because we love entertainment, but what are we doing to the victim? “We’re taking away the power of others. This campaign is about using your special power to raise your voice and make a difference. “You can change the lives of people around you,” said Wastie. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
